name: dfareporting
title: DCM/DFA Reporting And Trafficking API
description: Manages your DoubleClick Campaign Manager ad campaigns and reports.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

fields.name: additionalKeyValues
fields.desc: Additional key-values to be included in tags. Each key-value pair must be of the form key=value, and pairs must be separated by a semicolon (;). Keys and values must not contain commas. For example, id=2;color=red is a valid value for this field.

fields.name: includeClickThroughUrls
fields.desc: Whether static landing page URLs should be included in the tags. This setting applies only to placements.

fields.name: includeClickTracking
fields.desc: Whether click-tracking string should be included in the tags.

fields.name: keywordOption
fields.desc: Option specifying how keywords are embedded in ad tags. This setting can be used to specify whether keyword placeholders are inserted in placement tags for this site. Publishers can then add keywords to those placeholders.

schemas.name: ChangeLog
schemas.desc: Describes a change that a user has made to a resource.

fields.name: subaccountId
fields.desc: Subaccount ID of the modified object.

fields.name: userProfileId
fields.desc: ID of the user who modified the object.

fields.name: action
fields.desc: Action which caused the change.

fields.name: changeTime
fields.desc: Time when the object was modified.

fields.name: fieldName
fields.desc: Field name of the object which changed.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#changeLog".

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of this change log.

fields.name: newValue
fields.desc: New value of the object field.

fields.name: oldValue
fields.desc: Old value of the object field.

fields.name: userProfileName
fields.desc: User profile name of the user who modified the object.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account ID of the modified object.

fields.name: objectId
fields.desc: ID of the object of this change log. The object could be a campaign, placement, ad, or other type.

fields.name: objectType
fields.desc: Object type of the change log.

fields.name: transactionId
fields.desc: Transaction ID of this change log. When a single API call results in many changes, each change will have a separate ID in the change log but will share the same transactionId.

schemas.name: City
schemas.desc: Contains information about a city that can be targeted by ads.

fields.name: dartId
fields.desc: DART ID of this city. This is the ID used for targeting and generating reports.

fields.name: metroDmaId
fields.desc: ID of the metro region (DMA) to which this city belongs.

fields.name: regionCode
fields.desc: Region code of the region to which this city belongs.

fields.name: regionDartId
fields.desc: DART ID of the region to which this city belongs.

fields.name: countryCode
fields.desc: Country code of the country to which this city belongs.

fields.name: countryDartId
fields.desc: DART ID of the country to which this city belongs.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#city".

fields.name: metroCode
fields.desc: Metro region code of the metro region (DMA) to which this city belongs.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this city.

fields.name: backupImageTargetWindow
fields.desc: Target window for backup image. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE and HTML5_BANNER. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: compatibility
fields.desc:
Compatibilities associated with this creative. This is a read-only field. DISPLAY and DISPLAY_INTERSTITIAL refer to rendering either on desktop or on mobile devices or in mobile apps for regular or interstitial ads, respectively. APP and APP_INTERSTITIAL are for rendering in mobile apps. Only pre-existing creatives may have these compatibilities since new creatives will either be assigned DISPLAY or DISPLAY_INTERSTITIAL instead. IN_STREAM_VIDEO refers to rendering in in-stream video ads developed with the VAST standard. Applicable to all creative types.

Acceptable values are:
- "APP"
- "APP_INTERSTITIAL"
- "IN_STREAM_VIDEO"
- "DISPLAY"
- "DISPLAY_INTERSTITIAL"

fields.name: htmlCodeLocked
fields.desc: Whether HTML code is DCM-generated or manually entered. Set to true to ignore changes to htmlCode. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE and HTML5_BANNER.

fields.name: skipOffset
fields.desc: Amount of time to play the video before the skip button appears. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO.

fields.name: studioCreativeId
fields.desc: Studio creative ID associated with rich media and VPAID creatives. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: thirdPartyRichMediaImpressionsUrl
fields.desc: Third-party URL used to record rich media impressions. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

fields.name: artworkType
fields.desc: Type of artwork used for the creative. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: requiredFlashPluginVersion
fields.desc: The minimum required Flash plugin version for this creative. For example, 11.2.202.235. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: subaccountId
fields.desc: Subaccount ID of this creative. This field, if left unset, will be auto-generated for both insert and update operations. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of the creative. This is a required field and must be less than 256 characters long. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: creativeAssets
fields.desc: Assets associated with a creative. Applicable to all but the following creative types: INTERNAL_REDIRECT, INTERSTITIAL_INTERNAL_REDIRECT, and REDIRECT

fields.name: customKeyValues
fields.desc: Custom key-values for a Rich Media creative. Key-values let you customize the creative settings of a Rich Media ad running on your site without having to contact the advertiser. You can use key-values to dynamically change the look or functionality of a creative. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Size associated with this creative. When inserting or updating a creative either the size ID field or size width and height fields can be used. This is a required field when applicable; however for IMAGE, FLASH_INPAGE creatives, and for DISPLAY creatives with a primary asset of type HTML_IMAGE, if left blank, this field will be automatically set using the actual size of the associated image assets. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY, DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER, IMAGE, and all RICH_MEDIA.

fields.name: studioAdvertiserId
fields.desc: Studio advertiser ID associated with rich media and VPAID creatives. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: adParameters
fields.desc: Ad parameters user for VPAID creative. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all VPAID.

fields.name: backupImageClickThroughUrl
fields.desc: Click-through URL for backup image. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE and HTML5_BANNER. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: timerCustomEvents
fields.desc: List of timer events configured for the creative. For DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY creatives, these are read-only and auto-generated from clickTags. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: active
fields.desc: Whether the creative is active. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: creativeFieldAssignments
fields.desc: Creative field assignments for this creative. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#creative".

fields.name: overrideCss
fields.desc: Override CSS value for rich media creatives. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

fields.name: videoDescription
fields.desc: Description of the video ad. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

fields.name: companionCreatives
fields.desc: List of companion creatives assigned to an in-Stream videocreative. Acceptable values include IDs of existing flash and image creatives. Applicable to the following creative types: all VPAID and all INSTREAM_VIDEO with dynamicAssetSelection set to false.

fields.name: allowScriptAccess
fields.desc: Whether script access is allowed for this creative. This is a read-only and deprecated field which will automatically be set to true on update. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE.

fields.name: auto_advance_images
fields.desc: Whether images are automatically advanced for image gallery creatives. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY.

fields.name: backupImageReportingLabel
fields.desc: Reporting label used for HTML5 banner backup image. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: clickTags
fields.desc: Click tags of the creative. For DISPLAY, FLASH_INPAGE, and HTML5_BANNER creatives, this is a subset of detected click tags for the assets associated with this creative. After creating a flash asset, detected click tags will be returned in the creativeAssetMetadata. When inserting the creative, populate the creative clickTags field using the creativeAssetMetadata.clickTags field. For DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY creatives, there should be exactly one entry in this list for each image creative asset. A click tag is matched with a corresponding creative asset by matching the clickTag.name field with the creativeAsset.assetIdentifier.name field. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: dynamicAssetSelection
fields.desc: Set this to true to enable the use of rules to target individual assets in this creative. When set to true creativeAssetSelection must be set. This also controls asset-level companions. When this is true, companion creatives should be assigned to creative assets. Learn more. Applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO creatives.

fields.name: version
fields.desc: The version number helps you keep track of multiple versions of your creative in your reports. The version number will always be auto-generated during insert operations to start at 1. For tracking creatives the version cannot be incremented and will always remain at 1. For all other creative types the version can be incremented only by 1 during update operations. In addition, the version will be automatically incremented by 1 when undergoing Rich Media creative merging. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: advertiserId
fields.desc: Advertiser ID of this creative. This is a required field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: lastModifiedInfo
fields.desc: Creative last modification information. This is a read-only field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: renderingId
fields.desc: ID of current rendering version. This is a read-only field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: studioTraffickedCreativeId
fields.desc: Studio trafficked creative ID associated with rich media and VPAID creatives. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: videoDuration
fields.desc: Creative video duration in seconds. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: INSTREAM_VIDEO, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: adTagKeys
fields.desc: Keywords for a Rich Media creative. Keywords let you customize the creative settings of a Rich Media ad running on your site without having to contact the advertiser. You can use keywords to dynamically change the look or functionality of a creative. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: fsCommand
fields.desc: OpenWindow FSCommand of this creative. This lets the SWF file communicate with either Flash Player or the program hosting Flash Player, such as a web browser. This is only triggered if allowScriptAccess field is true. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE.

fields.name: progressOffset
fields.desc: Amount of time to play the video before counting a view. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO.

fields.name: skippable
fields.desc: Whether the user can choose to skip the creative. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

fields.name: sslCompliant
fields.desc: Whether the creative is SSL-compliant. This is a read-only field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: sslOverride
fields.desc: Whether creative should be treated as SSL compliant even if the system scan shows it's not. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: counterCustomEvents
fields.desc: List of counter events configured for the creative. For DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY creatives, these are read-only and auto-generated from clickTags. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: thirdPartyBackupImageImpressionsUrl
fields.desc: Third-party URL used to record backup image impressions. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

fields.name: latestTraffickedCreativeId
fields.desc: Latest Studio trafficked creative ID associated with rich media and VPAID creatives. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: redirectUrl
fields.desc: URL of hosted image or hosted video or another ad tag. For INSTREAM_VIDEO_REDIRECT creatives this is the in-stream video redirect URL. The standard for a VAST (Video Ad Serving Template) ad response allows for a redirect link to another VAST 2.0 or 3.0 call. This is a required field when applicable. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_REDIRECT, INTERNAL_REDIRECT, INTERSTITIAL_INTERNAL_REDIRECT, and INSTREAM_VIDEO_REDIRECT

fields.name: thirdPartyUrls
fields.desc: Third-party URLs for tracking in-stream video creative events. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

fields.name: backupImageFeatures
fields.desc: List of feature dependencies that will cause a backup image to be served if the browser that serves the ad does not support them. Feature dependencies are features that a browser must be able to support in order to render your HTML5 creative asset correctly. This field is initially auto-generated to contain all features detected by DCM for all the assets of this creative and can then be modified by the client. To reset this field, copy over all the creativeAssets' detected features. Applicable to the following creative types: HTML5_BANNER. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: authoringSource
fields.desc: Source application where creative was authored. Presently, only DBM authored creatives will have this field set. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: commercialId
fields.desc: Industry standard ID assigned to creative for reach and frequency. Applicable to the following creative types: all INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

fields.name: convertFlashToHtml5
fields.desc: Whether Flash assets associated with the creative need to be automatically converted to HTML5. This flag is enabled by default and users can choose to disable it if they don't want the system to generate and use HTML5 asset for this creative. Applicable to the following creative type: FLASH_INPAGE. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: creativeAssetSelection
fields.desc: Required if dynamicAssetSelection is true.

fields.name: idDimensionValue
fields.desc: Dimension value for the ID of this creative. This is a read-only field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: archived
fields.desc: Whether the creative is archived. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: totalFileSize
fields.desc: Combined size of all creative assets. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID.

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
Type of this creative. This is a required field. Applicable to all creative types.

Note: FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER, and IMAGE are only used for existing creatives. New creatives should use DISPLAY as a replacement for these types.

fields.name: authoringTool
fields.desc: Authoring tool for HTML5 banner creatives. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: HTML5_BANNER.

fields.name: backgroundColor
fields.desc: The 6-character HTML color code, beginning with #, for the background of the window area where the Flash file is displayed. Default is white. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE.

fields.name: htmlCode
fields.desc: HTML code for the creative. This is a required field when applicable. This field is ignored if htmlCodeLocked is false. Applicable to the following creative types: all CUSTOM, FLASH_INPAGE, and HTML5_BANNER, and all RICH_MEDIA.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of this creative. This is a read-only, auto-generated field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: renderingIdDimensionValue
fields.desc: Dimension value for the rendering ID of this creative. This is a read-only field. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: requiredFlashVersion
fields.desc: The internal Flash version for this creative as calculated by DoubleClick Studio. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account ID of this creative. This field, if left unset, will be auto-generated for both insert and update operations. Applicable to all creative types.

fields.name: exitCustomEvents
fields.desc: List of exit events configured for the creative. For DISPLAY and DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY creatives, these are read-only and auto-generated from clickTags, For DISPLAY, an event is also created from the backupImageReportingLabel. Applicable to the following creative types: DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

schemas.name: CreativeField
schemas.desc: Contains properties of a creative field.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of this creative field. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#creativeField".

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this creative field. This is a required field and must be less than 256 characters long and unique among creative fields of the same advertiser.

fields.name: subaccountId
fields.desc: Subaccount ID of this creative field. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account ID of this creative field. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

fields.name: advertiserId
fields.desc: Advertiser ID of this creative field. This is a required field on insertion.

fields.name: advertiserIdDimensionValue
fields.desc: Dimension value for the ID of the advertiser. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

fields.name: creativeFieldValues
fields.desc: Creative field value collection.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#creativeFieldValuesListResponse".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: daysOfWeek
fields.desc:
Days of the week when the ad will serve.

Acceptable values are:
- "SUNDAY"
- "MONDAY"
- "TUESDAY"
- "WEDNESDAY"
- "THURSDAY"
- "FRIDAY"
- "SATURDAY"

fields.name: hoursOfDay
fields.desc: Hours of the day when the ad will serve. Must be an integer between 0 and 23 (inclusive), where 0 is midnight to 1 AM, and 23 is 11 PM to midnight. Can be specified with days of week, in which case the ad would serve during these hours on the specified days. For example, if Monday, Wednesday, Friday are the days of week specified and 9-10am, 3-5pm (hours 9, 15, and 16) is specified, the ad would serve Monday, Wednesdays, and Fridays at 9-10am and 3-5pm.

fields.name: userLocalTime
fields.desc: Whether or not to use the user's local time. If false, the America/New York time zone applies.

fields.name: inventoryItems
fields.desc: Inventory item collection

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#inventoryItemsListResponse".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#operatingSystemVersionsListResponse".

fields.name: operatingSystemVersions
fields.desc: Operating system version collection.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: placementGroups
fields.desc: Placement group collection.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#placementGroupsListResponse".

fields.name: placementStrategies
fields.desc: Placement strategy collection.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#placementStrategiesListResponse".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#placementsGenerateTagsResponse".

fields.name: placementTags
fields.desc: Set of generated tags for the specified placements.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#userRolesListResponse".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: userRoles
fields.desc: User role collection.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#videoFormatsListResponse".

fields.name: videoFormats
fields.desc: Video format collection.

fields.name: creativeAssignments
fields.desc: Creative assignments in this creative rotation.

fields.name: creativeOptimizationConfigurationId
fields.desc: Creative optimization configuration that is used by this ad. It should refer to one of the existing optimization configurations in the ad's campaign. If it is unset or set to 0, then the campaign's default optimization configuration will be used for this ad.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of creative rotation. Can be used to specify whether to use sequential or random rotation.

fields.name: weightCalculationStrategy
fields.desc: Strategy for calculating weights. Used with CREATIVE_ROTATION_TYPE_RANDOM.

fields.name: iFrameFooter
fields.desc: Header text for iFrames for this site. Must be less than or equal to 2000 characters long.

fields.name: iFrameHeader
fields.desc: Header text for iFrames for this site. Must be less than or equal to 2000 characters long.

schemas.name: CustomRichMediaEvents
schemas.desc: Represents a Custom Rich Media Events group.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of resource this is, in this case dfareporting#customRichMediaEvents.

fields.name: filteredEventIds
fields.desc: List of custom rich media event IDs. Dimension values must be all of type dfa:richMediaEventTypeIdAndName.

schemas.name: OperatingSystemVersion
schemas.desc: Contains information about a particular version of an operating system that can be targeted by ads.

fields.name: operatingSystem
fields.desc: Operating system of this operating system version.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of this operating system version.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#operatingSystemVersion".

fields.name: majorVersion
fields.desc: Major version (leftmost number) of this operating system version.

fields.name: minorVersion
fields.desc: Minor version (number after the first dot) of this operating system version.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of this operating system version.

fields.name: orders
fields.desc: Order collection.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#ordersListResponse".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

fields.name: customHtml
fields.desc: User-entered value.

fields.name: targetWindowOption
fields.desc: Type of browser window for which the backup image of the flash creative can be displayed.

fields.name: weight
fields.desc: Weight of the creative assignment, applicable when the rotation type is CREATIVE_ROTATION_TYPE_RANDOM.

fields.name: active
fields.desc: Whether this creative assignment is active. When true, the creative will be included in the ad's rotation.

fields.name: creativeGroupAssignments
fields.desc: Creative group assignments for this creative assignment. Only one assignment per creative group number is allowed for a maximum of two assignments.

fields.name: creativeIdDimensionValue
fields.desc: Dimension value for the ID of the creative. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: Date and time that the assigned creative should stop serving. Must be later than the start time.

fields.name: richMediaExitOverrides
fields.desc:
Rich media exit overrides for this creative assignment.
Applicable when the creative type is any of the following: 
- RICH_MEDIA_INPAGE
- RICH_MEDIA_INPAGE_FLOATING
- RICH_MEDIA_IM_EXPAND
- RICH_MEDIA_EXPANDING
- RICH_MEDIA_INTERSTITIAL_FLOAT
- RICH_MEDIA_MOBILE_IN_APP
- RICH_MEDIA_MULTI_FLOATING
- RICH_MEDIA_PEEL_DOWN
- ADVANCED_BANNER
- VPAID_LINEAR
- VPAID_NON_LINEAR

fields.name: sequence
fields.desc: Sequence number of the creative assignment, applicable when the rotation type is CREATIVE_ROTATION_TYPE_SEQUENTIAL.

fields.name: sslCompliant
fields.desc: Whether the creative to be assigned is SSL-compliant. This is a read-only field that is auto-generated when the ad is inserted or updated.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: Date and time that the assigned creative should start serving.

fields.name: applyEventTags
fields.desc: Whether applicable event tags should fire when this creative assignment is rendered. If this value is unset when the ad is inserted or updated, it will default to true for all creative types EXCEPT for INTERNAL_REDIRECT, INTERSTITIAL_INTERNAL_REDIRECT, and INSTREAM_VIDEO.

fields.name: clickThroughUrl
fields.desc: Click-through URL of the creative assignment.

fields.name: companionCreativeOverrides
fields.desc: Companion creative overrides for this creative assignment. Applicable to video ads.

fields.name: creativeId
fields.desc: ID of the creative to be assigned. This is a required field.

fields.name: endDate
fields.desc: Placement end date. This date must be later than, or the same day as, the placement start date, but not later than the campaign end date. If, for example, you set 6/25/2015 as both the start and end dates, the effective placement date is just that day only, 6/25/2015. The hours, minutes, and seconds of the end date should not be set, as doing so will result in an error. This field is required on insertion.

fields.name: flighted
fields.desc: Whether this placement is flighted. If true, pricing periods will be computed automatically.

fields.name: floodlightActivityId
fields.desc: Floodlight activity ID associated with this placement. This field should be set when placement pricing type is set to PRICING_TYPE_CPA.

fields.name: pricingType
fields.desc: Placement pricing type. This field is required on insertion.

fields.name: startDate
fields.desc: Placement start date. This date must be later than, or the same day as, the campaign start date. The hours, minutes, and seconds of the start date should not be set, as doing so will result in an error. This field is required on insertion.

fields.name: capCostOption
fields.desc: Placement cap cost option.

fields.name: disregardOverdelivery
fields.desc: Whether cap costs are ignored by ad serving.

fields.name: pricingPeriods
fields.desc: Pricing periods for this placement.

fields.name: testingStartDate
fields.desc: Testing start date of this placement. The hours, minutes, and seconds of the start date should not be set, as doing so will result in an error.

fields.name: thirdPartyUrlType
fields.desc: Third-party URL type for in-stream video creatives.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: URL for the specified third-party URL type.

schemas.name: VideoFormat
schemas.desc: Contains information about supported video formats.

fields.name: resolution
fields.desc: The resolution of this video format.

fields.name: targetBitRate
fields.desc: The target bit rate of this video format.

fields.name: fileType
fields.desc: File type of the video format.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of the video format.

fields.name: kind

BACKUP_IMAGE applies to FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID creatives. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.
ADDITIONAL_IMAGE and ADDITIONAL_FLASH apply to FLASH_INPAGE creatives.
OTHER refers to assets from sources other than DCM, such as Studio uploaded assets, applicable to all RICH_MEDIA and all VPAID creatives.
PARENT_VIDEO refers to videos uploaded by the user in DCM and is applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO and VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives.
TRANSCODED_VIDEO refers to videos transcoded by DCM from PARENT_VIDEO assets and is applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO and VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives.
ALTERNATE_VIDEO refers to the DCM representation of child asset videos from Studio, and is applicable to VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives. These cannot be added or removed within DCM.
For VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives, PARENT_VIDEO, TRANSCODED_VIDEO and ALTERNATE_VIDEO assets that are marked active serve as backup in case the VPAID creative cannot be served. Only PARENT_VIDEO assets can be added or removed for an INSTREAM_VIDEO or VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creative.

schemas.name: AccountUserProfile
schemas.desc: AccountUserProfiles contains properties of a DCM user profile. This resource is specifically for managing user profiles, whereas UserProfiles is for accessing the API.

fields.name: comments
fields.desc: Comments for this user profile.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: ID of the user profile. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

fields.desc: Trafficker type of this user profile.

fields.name: userAccessType
fields.desc: User type of the user profile. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

fields.name: active
fields.desc: Whether this user profile is active. This defaults to false, and must be set true on insert for the user profile to be usable.

fields.name: advertiserFilter
fields.desc: Filter that describes which advertisers are visible to the user profile.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: Email of the user profile. The email addresss must be linked to a Google Account. This field is required on insertion and is read-only after insertion.

fields.name: locale
fields.desc:
Locale of the user profile. This is a required field.
Acceptable values are:  
- "cs" (Czech) 
- "de" (German) 
- "en" (English) 
- "en-GB" (English United Kingdom) 
- "es" (Spanish) 
- "fr" (French) 
- "it" (Italian) 
- "ja" (Japanese) 
- "ko" (Korean) 
- "pl" (Polish) 
- "pt-BR" (Portuguese Brazil)
- "ru" (Russian) 
- "sv" (Swedish) 
- "tr" (Turkish) 
- "zh-CN" (Chinese Simplified) 
- "zh-TW" (Chinese Traditional)

fields.name: siteFilter
fields.desc: Filter that describes which sites are visible to the user profile.

fields.name: subaccountId
fields.desc: Subaccount ID of the user profile. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

fields.name: userRoleFilter
fields.desc: Filter that describes which user roles are visible to the user profile.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account ID of the user profile. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

fields.name: campaignFilter
fields.desc: Filter that describes which campaigns are visible to the user profile.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#accountUserProfile".

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of the user profile. This is a required field. Must be less than 64 characters long, must be globally unique, and cannot contain whitespace or any of the following characters: "&;"#%,".

fields.name: userRoleId
fields.desc: User role ID of the user profile. This is a required field.

fields.name: landingPageId
fields.desc: ID of the landing page for the click-through URL. Applicable if the defaultLandingPage field is set to false.

fields.name: computedClickThroughUrl
fields.desc:
Read-only convenience field representing the actual URL that will be used for this click-through. The URL is computed as follows: 
- If defaultLandingPage is enabled then the campaign's default landing page URL is assigned to this field.
- If defaultLandingPage is not enabled and a landingPageId is specified then that landing page's URL is assigned to this field.
- If neither of the above cases apply, then the customClickThroughUrl is assigned to this field.

fields.name: customClickThroughUrl
fields.desc: Custom click-through URL. Applicable if the defaultLandingPage field is set to false and the landingPageId field is left unset.

fields.name: defaultLandingPage
fields.desc: Whether the campaign default landing page is used.

schemas.name: CreativeAssetSelection
schemas.desc: Encapsulates the list of rules for asset selection and a default asset in case none of the rules match. Applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO creatives.

fields.name: defaultAssetId
fields.desc: A creativeAssets[].id. This should refer to one of the parent assets in this creative, and will be served if none of the rules match. This is a required field.

fields.name: rules
fields.desc: Rules determine which asset will be served to a viewer. Rules will be evaluated in the order in which they are stored in this list. This list must contain at least one rule. Applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO creatives.

fields.name: frequencyCap
fields.desc: Limit on the number of times an individual user can be served the ad within a specified period of time.

fields.name: hardCutoff
fields.desc: Whether or not hard cutoff is enabled. If true, the ad will not serve after the end date and time. Otherwise the ad will continue to be served until it has reached its delivery goals.

fields.name: impressionRatio
fields.desc: Impression ratio for this ad. This ratio determines how often each ad is served relative to the others. For example, if ad A has an impression ratio of 1 and ad B has an impression ratio of 3, then DCM will serve ad B three times as often as ad A. Must be between 1 and 10.

fields.name: priority
fields.desc: Serving priority of an ad, with respect to other ads. The lower the priority number, the greater the priority with which it is served.

schemas.name: DynamicTargetingKey
schemas.desc: Contains properties of a dynamic targeting key. Dynamic targeting keys are unique, user-friendly labels, created at the advertiser level in DCM, that can be assigned to ads, creatives, and placements and used for targeting with DoubleClick Studio dynamic creatives. Use these labels instead of numeric DCM IDs (such as placement IDs) to save time and avoid errors in your dynamic feeds.

fields.name: objectId
fields.desc: ID of the object of this dynamic targeting key. This is a required field.

fields.name: objectType
fields.desc: Type of the object of this dynamic targeting key. This is a required field.
